{"id": "food_FOOD00022", "name": "Oat (food medium)", "category": "food", "organism_scope": "food microbiome / general", "aerobic": true, "description": "Food-derived medium: metabolizable components of Oat (Avena sativa) [Cereals and cereal products] from FooDB, plus a standard M9 mineral base. Organic components use presence-based uptake bounds; FooDB content retained. Measured compounds with no BiGG exchange are listed under uncovered.", "namespace": "bigg", "provenance": {"source_type": "database", "citation": "FooDB v2020-04-07 (Wishart DS et al., foodb.ca). Content sources: DTU, DUKE, MANUAL, PHENOL EXPLORER, USDA.", "doi": "", "url": "https://foodb.ca/downloads", "notes": "Organic components mapped from FooDB compounds to BiGG via InChIKey/name. Mineral base added. Bounds presence-based; foodb_content retained. Unmapped measured compounds kept in uncovered (v2 completeness fix). IMPORTANT: composition values are taken from the archived FooDB 2020-04-07 CSV data release; FooDB's live food page no longer displays this bulk composition, so it will appear empty. Verify individual compounds via the per-component cross-reference links. Underlying content was aggregated by FooDB from USDA / DTU / Phenol Explorer.", "data_release": "FooDB 2020-04-07 CSV release (foodb.ca/downloads)", "food_record": "https://foodb.ca/foods/FOOD00022", "verification": "expert-curated (multi-source food composition; growth-relevant profile completed, FooDB noise removed)", "curation_date": "2026-07-17", "curation_sources": ["USDA FoodData Central FDC 169705 (Oats, SR Legacy) — proximates, amino acids, minerals, vitamins, fatty-acid classes", "USDA / nutritionvalue.org NDB 57602100 (Oats, raw) — selenium, vitamin E, vitamin K, total sugars", "Yadessa et al. 2021, PMC8361264 — oxalate, phytate, tannin, mineral ranges of oat grain", "Alemayehu et al. 2023, The Scientific World Journal doi:10.1155/2023/2730175 — starch fraction, free-sugar and beta-glucan composition", "Beta-glucan range: PMC9269010, PMC7765213", "FooDB FOOD00022 (original component list)"], "curation_notes": "Oat is a starch-dominated dry cereal grain: the overwhelming carbon/energy source is starch (~58 g/100g, ~85% of carbohydrate), followed by beta-glucan (~4 g) and other fibre; free sugars are low (~1 g, mostly sucrose). Unlike fruit foods, oat has minimal free organic acids — oxalic and phytic acid are the only well-quantified ones. Protein is high (~17 g) and glutamate-rich. Removed four animal-derived metabolites (creatine, taurine, dopamine, serotonin) as biologically implausible FooDB noise;", "curation_added": ["L-valine (essential AA absent from current profile)", "D-fructose (specific free sugar)", "palmitic acid 16:0 (main SFA)", "beta-glucan (defining oat soluble carbohydrate)", "starch quantified (dominant carbon source)", "oxalic acid (organic acid)", "phytic acid (dominant organic phosphate/acid)", "selenium amount, biotin amount, choline amount", "quantitative amounts for all amino acids, minerals, vitamins, fatty acids"], "curation_removed": [{"name": "Creatine cytosol", "reason": "animal muscle metabolite, biologically implausible in a plant grain; FooDB predicted/contaminant"}, {"name": "Taurine C2H7NO3S", "reason": "animal-derived sulfonic amino acid, not synthesized by cereals; FooDB predicted"}, {"name": "Dopamine", "reason": "animal catecholamine neurotransmitter; not a growth nutrient of oat, trace/predicted FooDB entry"}, {"name": "Serotonin", "reason": "animal indoleamine neurotransmitter; implausible as an oat nutrient, FooDB predicted"}, {"name": "CO2 CO2", "reason": "medium scaffolding gas, not a food-derived nutrient (drop from composition list)"}, {"name": "O2 O2", "reason": "medium scaffolding gas, not a food-derived nutrient"}], "curation_confidence": "high"}, "components": [{"name": "starch", "bigg_metabolite": "starch", "exchange": "EX_starch_e", "lower_bound": -10.0, "upper_bound": 1000.0, "concentration_mM": null, "xref": {"kegg": "C00369", "che